text: As a proud South African, I'mÂ  happy there is another movie with African themes and references. I feel proud too find all the SA easter eggs in his films. All these comments hating on this movie. This movie is and Neill Blomkamp career isn't so much about making movies that win every award under the sun. It's about bring South Africa, and basically, a dying culture alive again. People have no idea about South Africa in general, so this movie, along with all his other movies open peoples eyes up a bit. You can even google and interview with Neill Blomkamp about that.

I've seen District 9 and this trailer gives me the same feeling: that thing looks so surreal that it might really happen soon! But I Robot is kinda too advanced and too computer animated to build up the rapport with audience.Â

text: Man I want this to be great so much. Blomkamp, Ninja and Yolandi are real artists with heart. South Africa is not like Hollywood. They deserve it. Next Level Shit.Â Throw in Ripley and ED-209, classic.  I'm scared though. I'm afraid it is going to be the same story as AI, Robocop, I Robot. EvilCorp creates robots to rule humanity, but the one good robot saves us and proves more humane than we.  I watched Elysium again recently, and it is not a bad movie. It was hyped too much and after District 9, we expected too much. Maybe this one looks a little off but will be a classic! (Man, there's a lot of artificial intelligence movies coming out!)
